---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <!-- The main container that gives us that dark blue background -->
  <div class="page-wrapper">
    
    <!-- BLOCK 1: Blue Brain Video & Main Title -->
    <section class="content-card two-column">
      <div class="media-col">
        <video autoplay loop muted playsinline class="responsive-video">
          <source src="/assets/videos/blue-glowing-brain-blue-light-electric-video.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        </video>
      </div>
      <div class="text-col align-center">
        <h1 class="main-title">The Neurotronic<br>Brain</h1>
        <hr class="title-divider" />
        <h2 class="subtitle">Edge-Native<br>Autonomous Systems</h2>
      </div>
    </section>

<section class="content-card padded-card two-column-fixed">
      
      <div class="left-col align-top">
        <h2 class="flight-title">First Flight:</h2>
        <h3 class="flight-subtitle"><em>The Neurotronic<br>Brain</em> Achieves<br>Full Autonomy</h3>
        
        <div class="demo-video-wrapper">
          <video controls class="demo-video">
            <source src="/assets/videos/neurobotics-neurotronic-brain-first-flight.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="right-col specs-text text-col align-top">
        <p>At Neurobotics, we have officially achieved "First Light" on the world's first bare-metal Silicon-Based Artificial Life Form (SBALF). By bridging the <em>Albus-Renshaw Theory of Deterministic Autonomy</em> with physical hardware, we have successfully engineered an air-gapped, deterministic silicon central nervous system capable of processing complex physical environments without a single call to a cloud data center.</p>
        <br>
        <p>By mapping true neuroanatomy directly onto a bare-metal RISC-V substrate, we have solved the vulnerabilities of probabilistic AI and delivered a mathematical architecture ready for contested Electronic Warfare (EW) environments.</p>
        
        <h4>Biomimetic Sensory Processing</h4>
        <p>True autonomy requires extreme low SWaP (Size, Weight, and Power) without sacrificing situational awareness. Our edge vision and sensory nodes operate natively on highly optimized local hardware, bypassing the need for cloud-tethered processing. Built for aerospace survivability, the sensory tier is guarded at the OS-level, ensuring instantaneous self-healing and kernel-level ruggedization against single-event upsets.</p>
        
        <h4>Biomimetic Data Efficiency</h4>
        <p>Traditional AI streams massive amounts of telemetry to the cloud, creating critical latency bottlenecks and severe EW vulnerability. The Neurotronic Brain mimics the extreme efficiency of biological neuroanatomy. It evaluates telemetry locally and broadcasts actionable deltas over a decentralized internal bus at biomimetic frequencies. Sensory nodes only alert the higher cognitive tiers when a significant environmental state change occurs, completely eliminating bandwidth bottlenecks and conserving physical power.</p>
        
        <h4>Deterministic Governance (The VSCC)</h4>
        <p>The highest cognitive tier—the executive Prefrontal Cortex—is driven by our Vector Symbolic Cognitive Core (VSCC). Eradicating the probabilistic LLM entirely, sensorimotor loops and executive reasoning now operate as mathematically auditable 10,000-Dimensional vector algebra executing at the speed of logic gates.</p>
        <br>
        <p>Executing this 10,000-D mathematics natively within the pure RISC-V CPU pipeline with Tier 1 physical FPGA loop integration, the chassis achieves a blistering, deterministic ~3ms evaluation and physical override time. No cloud. No black boxes. Just deterministic supremacy engineered for the absolute extremes.</p>
      </div>

    </section>
  </div> ```

  <style>
   /* --- THE CSS SPATIAL MAP --- */
  
  /* 1. The dark blue page background */
  .page-wrapper {
    background-color: #050a15; 
    padding: 60px 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 60px; 
  }

  /* 2. The black content cards - REMOVED PADDING */
  .content-card {
    background-color: #000000;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 1200px;
    border-radius: 8px; 
    overflow: hidden; /* CRUCIAL: This forces the video to respect the card's rounded corners! */
  }

  /* 3. The 50/50 CSS Grid */
  .two-column {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    align-items: stretch; /* Forces both columns to be the exact same height */
  }

  /* 4. Video Styling - THE CROP EFFECT */
  .media-col {
    height: 100%;
  }

  .responsive-video {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover; /* CRUCIAL: This perfectly crops the video to fill the space without squishing! */
    display: block; 
  }

  /* 5. Typography & Text Column Padding */
  .text-col {
    color: #e0e0e0;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 60px; /* We moved the padding here so the text has room to breathe */
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center; /* Vertically centers the text */
  }

  /* Aligning the first block text to the left like your Wix site */
  .align-center {
    text-align: left;
  }

  .main-title {
    font-size: 4rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  /* Left-aligns the divider line */
  .title-divider {
    width: 100%;
    border: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #4a5c73;
    margin: 0 0 20px 0; 
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: #cccccc;
  }

  .flight-title {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .flight-subtitle {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: #ffffff;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .specs-text h4 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #ffffff;
    margin-top: 30px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  
  .specs-text h4:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

 /* --- 6. STRICT 2-COLUMN LAYOUT (Row 2) --- */
  .two-column-fixed {
    display: grid;
    /* minmax(0, 1fr) stops the video from blowing out the grid! */
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    column-gap: 60px; 
  }

  .padded-card {
    padding: 60px; /* Restores the padding around the edge */
  }

  .left-col, .right-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .align-top {
    justify-content: flex-start;
    padding: 0; /* Overrides default text padding so it aligns at the top */
    width: 100%; 
  }

  .demo-video-wrapper {
    margin-top: 40px; /* Spacing between the "First Flight" text and the video */
    width: 100%;
  }

  .demo-video {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    background-color: #000;
  }

  /* Responsive adjustment for smaller screens */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .two-column {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr; /* Stacks the columns on mobile! */
    }
    .text-only {
      padding: 40px 20px;
    }
  }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>